A person has possible life-changing injuries after a crash involving several cars in Radstock, police said.
Officers were called to reports of a collision involving a BMW, three parked cars and a wall in Bath New Road at about 12:30 GMT on Friday.
One person was taken to hospital, according to Avon and Somerset Police.
The road reopened at 07:15 GMT, the force said. Anyone with dashcam footage, or who was in the area at the time, has been asked to contact police.
